---
export const prerender = true

import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import SiteNav from '@components/SiteNav.astro'
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Rules as Written" description="The story behind the Rules as Written D&D podcast — how a pub quiz in Beijing led to an international tabletop adventure.">
  <SiteNav />
  <main id="main" class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="mb-6" style="color: var(--color-primary);">About Rules as Written</h1>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="mb-4" style="font-size: var(--font-size-6);">Our Story</h2>
      <p>
        It all started at a pub quiz in Beijing. A group of expats, strangers at first, bonded over trivia and
        discovered a shared love of tabletop gaming. Before long, a D&D campaign was born — complete with
        homebrew worlds, memorable NPCs, and the kind of chaotic energy only a party of first-time players can bring.
      </p>
      <p>
        When life eventually scattered the group across different countries and time zones, the campaign didn't end.
        It adapted. Late-night video calls replaced the physical table, and the dice kept rolling. Somewhere between
        rules debates about grappling and passionate disagreements over spell components, someone said: "We should
        record this."
      </p>
      <p>
        And so <strong>Rules as Written</strong> was born — a podcast where we break down the rules of
        Dungeons & Dragons 5th Edition, one chapter at a time. We read the rules so you don't have to (but we think
        you should). Whether you're a seasoned DM or rolling your first character, we're here to help you understand
        the game we all love.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="mb-4" style="font-size: var(--font-size-6);">The Hosts</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-6">
        <div>
          <h3>JT Houk</h3>
          <p>
            Software engineer by day, dungeon master by night. JT built this website and handles the technical
            side of the podcast. When not coding or rolling dice, you'll find him exploring new cities or
            debating the finer points of action economy.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Toby</h3>
          <p>
            The voice of reason at the table (most of the time). Toby brings a methodical approach to rules
            analysis and a talent for finding the edge cases that make D&D both frustrating and wonderful.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="mb-4" style="font-size: var(--font-size-6);">Listen & Connect</h2>
      <p>
        Find us on <a href="https://open.spotify.com/show/3QsthThGhfigIwbGHauPfQ" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Spotify</a>,
        <a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/rules-as-written-a-d-d-podcast/id1545377455" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Apple Podcasts</a>,
        or wherever you get your podcasts. Got a topic suggestion or rules question?
        <a href="/contact">Drop us a line</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
